ontologyFramework.OFDataMapping.complexDataType

Class TimeLine

  • java.lang.Object
    • ontologyFramework.OFDataMapping.complexDataType.TimeLine
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, OFDataMapperInterface<org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual,TimeLine>

    public class TimeLine
extends java.lang.Object
implements OFDataMapperInterface<org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual,TimeLine>
    This class implements the mapping mechanism between an individual and a TimeLine object. Namely, it implements also the definition of a time line expressed as a list of TimeWindow. In particular, the idea is based over three predefined SWRL rules into the ontology: 
     TimeWindow(?c), Thing(?d), hasTypeTimeStamp(?d, ?t), 
	hasTypeTimeWindowsLowerBound(?c, ?l), hasTypeTimeWindowsUpperBound(?c, ?u), 
  greaterThan(?t, ?l), lessThan(?t, ?u) -> belongsToTimeWindows(?d, ?c)
 
 Clock(?ck), TimeWindow(?c), hasTypeTimeStamp(?ck, ?tck), 
  hasTypeTimeWindowsCentralInstant(?c, ?tc), hasTypeTimeWindowsSize(?c, ?w), 
  add(?a, ?t, ?w2), add(?t, ?tc, ?tck), divide(?w2, ?w, "2"^^long) 
  -> hasTypeTimeWindowsUpperBound(?c, ?a)
 
 Clock(?ck), TimeWindow(?c), hasTypeTimeStamp(?ck, ?tck), 
  hasTypeTimeWindowsCentralInstant(?c, ?tc), hasTypeTimeWindowsSize(?c, ?w), 
 	add(?t, ?tck, ?tc), divide(?w2, ?w, "2"^^long), subtract(?a, ?t, ?w2) 
 	-> hasTypeTimeWindowsLowerBound(?c, ?a)
    Thanks to which it is possible to move a TimeWindow only updating the clock value, defined as a Time Instance belong to the individual: C_SystemClock. Since it is useful to automatically build ontological classes to represent time windows in a way that an individual, which has a instant property, will be classified in the appropriate windows; a particular mechanism has been adopted. A time windows is defined through an individual IndBaseName-index which belongs to the class TimeWindow, since it has the following data property: "IndBaseName-index hasTypeTimeWindowesSize "20000"^^long" and "IndBaseName-index hasTypeTimeWindowsCentralInstant "-10000"^^long". When the reasoner is update it will apply the above SWRL rules to add two data property as: "IndBaseName-index hasTypeTimeWindowsUpperBound "1383042263107"^^long" and "IndBaseName-index hasTypeTimeWindowsLowerBound "1383042243107"^^long". Moreover, if an individual I will have a time stamp property such that it would be classified into a class associated to the individual IndBaseName-index the above SWRL rules will push the reasoner to add this object property: "I belongsToTimeWindows IndBaseName-index". To make those information working with a classification in ontological sense the following SWRL rules must be added: "Thing(?d), belongsToTimeWindows(?d, IndBaseName-index) -> ClassBaseName-index(?d)". Where the string "index" is preserved for human readability. Furthermore, this step require to create the class named ClassBaseName-indix that will be placed as a sub class of a root class named with a base class name. The proposes of this class is to make those steps automatically during the mapping between an ontology and the system. Also interesting is how to do it for a list of TimeWindows, and so for a time line. This can be done by some static methods of this class where two relative (with respect to the system clock) quantities are needed. Since Reaoner's updates can be also longer than a time line a cleaner pool can be added into the list. This is just a time window, and so it follows all the above consideration and it is allocated in the minimum index inside the time line (0). This particular windows should be big enough to guarantee that an eventually procedure, which is typically synchronized with the reasoner updating, can remove all the individuals that are gone through all the time line since they are just classified by the reaosoner inside the cleaning class. This class is created and initialized using OFDataMapperBuilder; furthermore, it can be retrieved through the static map manager: OFBuildedListInvoker. Actually, for thecnical problem the methods replaceIntoOntology(OWLNamedIndividual, TimeLine, TimeLine, OWLReferences) is not implemented.

        Creates a new succession of TimeWindow to be mapped between ontology and the system. This constructor should be used to define time lines from api since it doesn not give a reference to the static class OFBuildedListInvoker used to retrieve primitive mapper to map a time line. After this call the time line is empty
        Parameters:

        classBaseName - a basic string to define the class which represent a time windows, In this documentation, during class introduction it has been called: "classBaseName".
        rootClass - ontological class to set as super class of all classes built in relation with "ClassBaseName-index".

      • addCleaner

        public void addCleaner(Procedure cleaner)
        Add a cleaning time windows with the index 0. It is recommended to do this operation when no more time windows have to be added in the line to avoid that the cleaner will move from its index. The cleaning pool is a time window with a fixed size: 1381786380L and a relative center computed in a way that the upper bound of the pool is conceded with the lower bound of the time windows which has index equal to 1 in the time line.
        Parameters:
        cleaner - procedure to remove individual from the cleaning pool.

      • mapNames

        public void mapNames()
        It just call mapNames(Procedure) with the parameter equal to null.

      • mapNames

        public void mapNames(Procedure cleaner)
        It maps all the names with their base string and their definitive index. It is recommended to do this operation when no more time windows have to be added in the line to avoid inconsistent index mapping. Moreover, if the parameter is not null, this methods add a cleaner to the time line using addCleaner(Procedure)
        Parameters:
        cleaner - the procedure to be associate to the cleaning pull. If it is null than no cleaning pool will be added.

      • getConstantTimeLine

        public static TimeLine getConstantTimeLine(java.lang.Long lowerLimit,
                           java.lang.Long highLimit,
                           java.lang.Long granularity,
                           java.lang.String baseClassName,
                           java.lang.String baseIndividualName,
                           org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLClass rootClass)
        This method return a time line with time windows already attached to it. In particolar the maximum temporal span of a time line is given through the parameters lowerLimit and higthLimit. This span will modified (in terms of milliseconds) to be divisible in an integer number of time windows that will have the same size during all the time line. The size is defined by the parameter granularity. No cleaner are attached to this time line and not name mapping is performed by this method.
        Parameters:
        lowerLimit - minimum relative (0 = now) temporal span in milliseconds.
        highLimit - maximum relative (0 = now) temporal span in milliseconds.
        granularity - size of all the time windows.
        baseClassName - a basic string to define the class which represent a time windows, In this documentation, during class introduction it has been called: "classBaseName".
        baseIndividualName - a basic string to define a time windows individual. In this documentation, during class introduction it has been called: "IndBaseName".
        rootClass - ontological class to set as super class of all classes built in relation with "ClassBaseName-index".
        Returns:
        a complete time line over a temporal span, where all the windows has equal size.

      • getSquareTimeLine

        public static TimeLine getSquareTimeLine(java.lang.Long lowerLimit,
                         java.lang.Long highLimit,
                         java.lang.Long granularity,
                         java.lang.Integer modularity,
                         java.lang.String baseClassName,
                         java.lang.String baseIndividualName,
                         org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLClass rootClass)
        This method return a time line with time windows already attached to it. In particular the maximum temporal span of a time line is given through the parameters lowerLimit and higthLimit. This span will modified (in terms of milliseconds) to be divisible in an integer number of time windows that will have the size which increases going further from the relative 0 value. The initial size is defined by the parameter granularity and follows the rule: granularity *= modularity; which is recursively computed for every time windows starting from the relative 0 and going up or down in the time axes. No cleaner are attached to this time line and not name mapping is performed by this method.
        Parameters:
        lowerLimit - minimum relative (0 = now) temporal span in milliseconds.
        highLimit - maximum relative (0 = now) temporal span in milliseconds.
        granularity - initial windows size
        modularity - multiplication factor for which the size increase going further from the relative center.
        baseClassName - a basic string to define the class which represent a time windows, In this documentation, during class introduction it has been called: "classBaseName".
        baseIndividualName - a basic string to define a time windows individual. In this documentation, during class introduction it has been called: "IndBaseName".
        rootClass - ontological class to set as super class of all classes built in relation with "ClassBaseName-index".
        Returns:
        a complete time line over a temporal span, where all the windows has size which increases going further from now.
